13:07.998 --> 13:10.365
You used to be
magnificent.

13:18.457 --> 13:20.542
Are you okay?

13:20.544 --> 13:24.429
Yeah, yeah, um,
I guess this, um,

13:24.431 --> 13:28.099
this pole-vaulting thing
is finally hitting me.

13:28.101 --> 13:29.184
I don't get it, Robin.

13:29.186 --> 13:31.886
Did you really want
to be a pole-vaulter?

13:31.888 --> 13:35.590
No, no, I was,
uh, I was always

13:35.592 --> 13:38.026
adamantly against having a...

13:38.028 --> 13:40.311
uh, a pole-vaulting career,

13:40.313 --> 13:42.430
even though it's
what most women want.

13:42.432 --> 13:44.816
Most women want
to be a pole-vaulter?

13:44.818 --> 13:46.985
In Canada--
it's very big up there.

13:46.987 --> 13:48.653
You know, it's,
it's meet a nice guy,

13:48.655 --> 13:51.456
get married, vault some poles,

13:51.458 --> 13:52.891
but I...

13:52.893 --> 13:55.460
never wanted that.

13:55.462 --> 13:57.778
Of course, it's one thing
not to want something.

13:57.780 --> 14:00.131
It's another to be told
you can't have it.

14:01.500 --> 14:03.218
I guess it's,
it's just nice knowing

14:03.220 --> 14:08.306
that you could someday do it
if you changed your mind.

14:09.742 --> 14:13.678
But now, all of a sudden,
that door is closed.

14:15.981 --> 14:19.417
What about the one where you ski
and shoot at the same time?

14:19.419 --> 14:21.653
That seems like something
you'd be good at.

14:23.189 --> 14:25.973
Oh, my God, Robin, look at this.

14:25.975 --> 14:27.659
O Cana-dorable!

14:27.661 --> 14:28.660
Am I right?

14:28.662 --> 14:30.195
Excuse me.

14:30.963 --> 14:33.665
Yep, this works.

14:37.922 --> 14:39.593
Scott, when I get

14:39.594 --> 14:40.893
down from here, you are going

14:40.895 --> 14:43.312
to be in big, big trouble,
mister.

14:43.314 --> 14:44.680
Come on, Mr. E.

14:44.682 --> 14:47.099
Didn't you ever cut loose
when you were a kid?

14:47.101 --> 14:49.518
That's irrelevant.

14:49.520 --> 14:51.937
I mean, of course I did.

14:51.939 --> 14:54.156
One time, when my parents
were out of town,

14:54.158 --> 14:58.244
my brothers and I set
the basement on fire

14:58.246 --> 15:01.447
hosting
an amateur wrestling exhibition.

15:02.565 --> 15:04.917
There were some theatrics.

15:04.919 --> 15:07.286
See, you get me.

15:07.288 --> 15:10.456
I don't think of you as some
dummy I trapped on the roof.

15:10.458 --> 15:14.627
I think of you more like,
like my dad.

15:16.046 --> 15:20.266
Can we keep the party going
for 30 more minutes, please?

15:22.886 --> 15:24.887
Okay, Scott.

15:24.889 --> 15:27.556
Thanks, Pop.

15:29.276 --> 15:33.145
It's fine, kid just needed
to blow off some steam.

15:40.436 --> 15:41.453
No!

15:41.455 --> 15:44.623
Grandma Gunderson knitted that!

15:44.625 --> 15:48.244
Scott...!

15:48.246 --> 15:49.628
That was crazy.

15:49.630 --> 15:51.964
She just ran
out of there crying.

15:51.966 --> 15:53.465
Now she's not
answering her phone.

15:53.467 --> 15:56.418
She's been acting really weird
for a few weeks now,

15:56.420 --> 16:00.422
really since the night
we discussed the hurricane.

16:00.424 --> 16:01.790
Barney, you split a cab home.

16:01.792 --> 16:03.342
Did she say anything?

16:06.313 --> 16:08.297
We didn't really talk much.

16:08.299 --> 16:09.398
Well, lucky for us,

16:09.400 --> 16:12.318
someone at this table is skilled

16:12.320 --> 16:15.070
in the art of detection.

16:15.855 --> 16:17.489
Robin's upset.

16:17.491 --> 16:20.326
She and Kevin
are having trouble.

16:20.328 --> 16:22.144
- He cheated on her.
- No way.

16:22.146 --> 16:25.831
Kevin's an honest, decent guy
who never on his best day

16:25.833 --> 16:27.816
could pull a hotter chick
than Robin.

16:27.818 --> 16:29.668
Maybe Robin cheated on him.

16:29.670 --> 16:33.488
Maybe Robin is the dirty bird
who slept with someone else.

16:33.490 --> 16:35.758
I don't know,
this pole-vaulting thing seems

16:35.760 --> 16:37.659
like a slam dunk to me.

16:37.661 --> 16:39.595
Oh, it is so obvious.

16:39.597 --> 16:40.930
Barney.

16:41.831 --> 16:43.015
What is the name of that guy

16:43.017 --> 16:44.683
you worked with-- uh, Randy?

16:44.685 --> 16:45.884
It was Randy.

16:45.886 --> 16:46.852
Wait a second.

16:46.854 --> 16:49.021
I just cracked this case.

16:50.274 --> 16:51.673
The little maple leaf onesie.

16:51.675 --> 16:53.609
<i>It made her homesick.</i>

16:53.611 --> 16:54.560
That's why she's so upset.

16:54.562 --> 16:55.644
She's not going home
for Christmas.

16:55.646 --> 16:58.147
She wants me
to invite her to Ohio.

16:58.149 --> 17:00.015
That's got to be it!

17:00.017 --> 17:02.067
Either that
or she slept with Barney.

