17:15.248 --> 17:17.800
Oh, you must be Scott.

17:17.801 --> 17:20.219
Oh, hello, ma'am.

17:20.221 --> 17:22.554
It's nice to finally
see your face.

17:22.556 --> 17:25.057
Well, I'd better go
hit those books.

17:25.059 --> 17:28.542
Hold it right there, young man.

17:29.346 --> 17:32.147
This is for helping out
my husband.

17:32.983 --> 17:35.651
Wow, 50 bucks.

17:35.653 --> 17:36.819
Merry Christmas.

17:45.745 --> 17:48.414
Lily!

17:48.416 --> 17:50.616
An airplane ticket
to Cleveland?

17:50.618 --> 17:52.618
I know it's not Canada,
but it starts with a "C"

17:52.620 --> 17:55.037
and it's cold as balls,
so get packed.

17:55.039 --> 17:56.755
You're coming home
with me for Christmas.

17:56.757 --> 17:58.507
Yeah, nice try, dude.

17:58.509 --> 17:59.541
I wouldn't go to Cleveland

17:59.543 --> 18:03.245
for $125 million
paid over six years.

18:03.247 --> 18:04.263
Still?

18:04.265 --> 18:05.848
Still with the LeBron jokes?

18:05.850 --> 18:07.099
Where's that ring, huh?

18:07.101 --> 18:09.101
Where's that ring
he's supposed to have by now?

18:09.969 --> 18:11.753
Look, I just-- I thought
you were bummed

18:11.755 --> 18:13.305
about not going home
for Christmas.

18:13.307 --> 18:14.423
Are you kidding?

18:14.425 --> 18:16.775
I love New York at Christmas.

18:16.777 --> 18:19.111
It's so quiet and peaceful.

18:20.196 --> 18:22.614
Got my eggnog to keep
me company, so...

18:22.616 --> 18:24.900
Robin, what's wrong?

18:24.902 --> 18:26.952
- Nothing.
- Just tell me.

18:26.954 --> 18:28.570
Why do you need
to know so bad?

18:28.572 --> 18:29.738
So I can cheer you up.

18:29.740 --> 18:31.273
It's not your job
to cheer me up.

18:31.275 --> 18:32.241
Yes, it is.

18:32.243 --> 18:34.326
Cheering you up is my job.

18:34.328 --> 18:36.161
Well, then, you're fired.

18:36.163 --> 18:37.162
You can't fire me.

18:37.164 --> 18:38.447
I'm union, bitch.

18:38.449 --> 18:39.915
It's not your job
to cheer me up.

18:39.917 --> 18:40.966
- Yes, it is.
- No, it's not.

18:40.968 --> 18:41.884
Yes, it is.

18:41.886 --> 18:43.452
No, it's not.

18:45.388 --> 18:47.789
Merry Christmas, Ted.

18:48.641 --> 18:50.843
Merry Christmas.

18:53.396 --> 18:57.766
<i>So, kids, I settled in</i>
<i>for a Christmas alone.</i>

18:57.768 --> 19:00.569
<i>I appreciated that Ted wanted</i>
<i>to cheer me up,</i>

19:00.571 --> 19:03.472
<i>but honestly,</i>
<i>it wasn't necessary.</i>

19:03.474 --> 19:05.441
<i>So I can't have kids.</i>

19:05.443 --> 19:07.192
<i>Big deal.</i>

19:07.194 --> 19:09.611
<i>This way there's no one</i>
<i>to hold me back in life,</i>

19:09.613 --> 19:11.246
<i>no one to keep me</i>
<i>from traveling</i>

19:11.248 --> 19:12.647
<i>where I want to travel,</i>

19:12.649 --> 19:14.500
<i>no one getting</i>
<i>in the way of my career.</i>

19:14.502 --> 19:17.319
<i>If you want to know</i>
<i>the truth of it,</i>

19:17.321 --> 19:20.155
<i>I'm glad you guys aren't real.</i>

19:33.970 --> 19:36.171
Really glad.

19:53.206 --> 19:55.374
Damn it.

19:56.527 --> 20:00.062
("Highway to Hell" by AC/DC
playing)

20:08.805 --> 20:11.706
Yes, it is.

20:12.875 --> 20:15.928
Look, you don't want to
tell me what's wrong, fine.

20:15.930 --> 20:17.229
I don't need to know.

20:18.331 --> 20:21.049
But you can never stop me
from trying to cheer you up.

20:22.018 --> 20:23.101
It's a fact of life.

20:23.103 --> 20:25.487
You're just gonna
have to deal with it.

20:25.489 --> 20:26.555
Ted...

20:26.557 --> 20:28.440
Hold on, hold on,
this is the best part.

20:30.293 --> 20:34.396
♪ I'm on the highway to hell ♪

20:34.398 --> 20:38.500
♪ On the highway to hell ♪

20:39.252 --> 20:42.955
♪ Highway to hell... ♪

20:42.957 --> 20:46.358
<i>Kids, your Aunt Robin</i>
<i>never became a pole-vaulter,</i>

20:46.360 --> 20:48.343
<i>but she did become</i>
<i>a famous journalist,</i>

20:48.345 --> 20:51.563
<i>a successful businesswoman,</i>
<i>a world traveler.</i>

20:51.565 --> 20:53.182
<i>She was even briefly</i>
<i>a bullfighter--</i>

20:53.184 --> 20:55.750
<i>that's a funny story,</i>
<i>I'll get to that one later.</i>

20:55.752 --> 20:59.721
<i>But there's one thing</i>
<i>your Aunt Robin never was.</i>

20:59.723 --> 21:00.755
<i>She was never alone.</i>

